{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, one column that stored temperature readings was named \"Temperature [Celsius]\", but GPT insisted on referring to it as \"temperature\".",
    "One categorical variable was \"out/in\", indicating if the record was an indoor or outdoor measurement, and ChatGPT used \"Indoor/Outdoor\" instead.",
    "As a result, the issue was detected in 21 scripts, combining all the test cases.",
    "Once they were fixed, 14 more Python scripts would be able to properly handle analysis tasks.",
    "On the other hand, ChatGPT displayed higher proficiency in the Python programming language."
  ]
}